Package org.jcatapult.mvc.parameter.el

Interface Summary
ExpressionEvaluator This interface defines the mechanism by which expressions are evaluated in order to get values from Objects and set values from the HTTP request parameters into Objects.
MethodVerifier This interface defines a mechanism for the MemberAccessor class to verify that a JavaBean method is valid.
 

Class Summary
Accessor This
Atom This class models a single atom in an expresion.
CollectionAccessor This class models a collection accessor during expression evaluation.
Context This
DefaultExpressionEvaluator This class is the default implementation of the ExpressionEvaluator service.
GetMethodVerifier This class verifies JavaBean standard getter methods.
IndexedAccessor This models a indexed property that takes a single parameter for the getter that is the index or key and two parameters for the setter, the index/key and value.
MemberAccessor This
PropertyInfo This class is a small helper class that is used to store the read and write methods of a bean property as well as a flag that determines if it is indexed.
PropertyName This class stores the information about JavaBean methods including the prefix and propertyName.
SetMethodVerifier This class verifies JavaBean standard setter methods.
TypeTools This is a toolkit that assists with generics.
 

Exception Summary
ExpressionException This is an exception that is thrown when expression processing fails.
